quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  70,40,It needs not that I swear by the Lord of the East and of the West that we have power
  70,41,"To replace them with better than themselves: neither are we to be hindered"
  70,42,"Wherefore let them flounder on and disport them, till they come face to face with their threatened day"
  70,43,The day on which they shall flock up out of their graves in haste like men who rally to a standard
  70,44,Their eyes downcast; disgrace shall cover them. Such their threatened day
  71,1,"We sent NOAH to his people, and said to him, \"Warn thou thy people ere there come on them an afflictive punishment"
  71,2,"He said, \"O my people! I come to you a plain-spoken warner"
  71,3,"Serve God and fear Him, and obey me"
  71,4,"Your sins will He forgive you, and respite you till the fixed Time; for when God's fixed Time hath come, it shall not be put back. Would that ye knew this"
  71,5,"He said, \"Lord I have cried to my people night and day"
  71,6,and my cry doth but make them flee from me the more
  71,7,"So oft as I cry to them, that thou mayest forgive them, they thrust their fingers into their ears, and wrap themselves in their garments, and persist in their error, and are disdainfully disdainful"
  71,8,Then I cried aloud to them
  71,9,"Then again spake I with plainness, and in private did I secretly address them"
  71,10,"And I said, Beg forgiveness of your Lord, for He is ready to forgive"